<section class="detail" id="t:stack_trim_fun/0">


  <div class="detail-header">
    <a href="#t:stack_trim_fun/0" class="detail-link" data-no-tooltip="" aria-label="Link to this type">
      <i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    </a>
    <div class="heading-with-actions">

      <div class="signature-row">

          <h1 class="signature" translate="no">stack_trim_fun()</h1>


          <span class="note">(since OTP 24.0)</span>


          <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/stdlib/src/erl_error.erl#L56" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow" aria-label="View Source">
            <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="docstring">



        <div class="specs">

            <pre translate="no"><span class="attribute">-type</span> stack_trim_fun() :: fun((<a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:module/0">module</a>(), <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:atom/0">atom</a>(), <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:arity/0">arity</a>()) -> <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:boolean/0">boolean</a>()).</pre>

        </div>


<p>A fun used to trim the end of the stacktrace. It is called with module,
function, and arity from an entry from the stacktrace. The fun is to return
<code class="inline">true</code> if the entry should be trimmed, and <code class="inline">false</code> otherwise. The default value
is:</p><pre><code class="text">fun(_, _, _) -&gt; false end</code></pre>
  </section>
</section>

